September is Suicide Prevention and Awareness month. I know y’all are used to always seeing the goofy, fun, laughing, side of Paulina, and I haven’t been super open about my mental health struggles but I thought I’d take a moment to get fairly personal.

I’ve struggled with chronic depression my entire life, it started when I was about 10. I’ve attempted suicide 4 times in my lifetime, and thank god, I didn’t succeed. I know what it’s like to feel alone, outta control and a burden. But I’m here to remind you; you are not any of those things, even though sometimes it feels like you are. Depression is an ongoing battle that I face daily. Whenever I feel myself getting down and going to that “dark place” I make it a habit to reach out to my friends, journal, meditate, move my body and believe me I am very vocal about my demons. Through a lot of continued healing and inner work I’ve had to learn that there is immense power in vulnerability. This is not a cry for help! I am very proud of the work I’ve put in to be where I am now. But I’ve had to work really damn hard for it! And I will continue to do so ☺️

Having emotions and feeling imperfect or broken at times is human. And trust me!! we need each other, we are biologically not meant to be alone in this world. That took me a long time to grasp, because I was raised to believe that feeling down and expressing it, was a sign of weakness and that I need to just “toughen up and deal with it” that was a harmful narrative. Some of the happiest people are the ones who are struggling the most. And that’s why it’s important to check on your loved ones, tell them you love them, often. you never know what battles they may be internally facing and friendly reminder; you are not weak or less then for having emotions, we all get down sometimes and it’s okay to admit that we need help to get back on our feet. You are loved, you are worthy and you matter so much, oh and therapy is fucking awesome!!! ❤️🫶🏽 #suicideprevention #suicideawarenessmonth thank you @asianmentalhealthproject for the resources
